Description: Gold boss; with stamped design of concentric semicircles round the edge; in centre feather of Isis between two crescent horns above a sun disk; four loops for attachment; piece of jewellery.
Bibliographic references: Jewellery / Catalogue of the Jewellery, Greek, Etruscan, and Roman, in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum. (2906)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (QB.11)
